S3 env vars

      - RUNNING_ENV=prod/integration
      - MARABUNTA_MODE=full
      - ODOO_CLOUD_PLATFORM_UNSAFE=true
      - AWS_HOST=sos.exo.io
      - AWS_BUCKETNAME=fluxdock-odoo-prod/integration
      - AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=(see LP)
      - AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=(see LP)


migration steps are:

1. restore db and filestore locally (as you have seen yesterday, 1st script)
2. modify env vars as above
3. run the instance to migrate to 9.2.1

3a: check filestore migration

select store_fname from ir_attachment;  # should show you the uris of the attachments **

4. dump the db to .pg (2nd script)
5. import the db on prod cluster (3rd script)

6. domain

add official one after comma, like:

    io.rancher.loadbalancer.target.alcyon-odoo-integration/odoo: integration.alcyon.odoo.camptocamp.ch:443=80,erp-integration.alcyonbelux.be:443=80

7. certificate

add it here: https://caas.camptocamp.net/env/1a19171/infra/certificates

NOTE: there's no way to renew it automatically and we don't get any warning for expiration


** this can be done with `s3cmd`

~/.s3cfg:

[default]
host_base = sos.exo.io
host_bucket = %(bucket)s.sos.exo.io
access_key = # put the key
secret_key = # put the key
use_https = True
signature_v2 = True


s3cmd ls s3://fluxdock-odoo-integration|prod
